cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

The paper deals with interleaving schemes for turbo codes, which are commonly used in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses practical aspects of the interleavers, such as memory requirements and decoding error probabilities, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper presents theoretical results on the minimum distance of the resulting turbo codes, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
